TITLE: Using useLocalStorage Hook in React Component
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates basic usage of useLocalStorage hook to manage a localStorage value with setValue and remove functions. Shows how to initialize, update, and remove a localStorage value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useLocalStorage.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useLocalStorage } from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  const [value, setValue, remove] = useLocalStorage('my-key', 'foo');

  return (
    <div>
      <div>Value: {value}</div>
      <button onClick={() => setValue('bar')}>bar</button>
      <button onClick={() => setValue('baz')}>baz</button>
      <button onClick={() => remove()}>Remove</button>
    </div>
  );
};
```

