TITLE: Implementing FIFO Queue with useQueue Hook in React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the useQueue hook from react-use to create a simple FIFO queue in a React component. It shows how to add and remove items from the queue, and display the first item, last item, and size of the queue.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useQueue.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { useQueue } from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  const { add, remove, first, last, size } = useQueue();

  return (
    <div>
      <ul>
        <li>first: {first}</li>
        <li>last: {last}</li>
        <li>size: {size}</li>
      </ul>
      <button onClick={() => add((last || 0) + 1)}>Add</button>
      <button onClick={() => remove()}>Remove</button>
    </div>
  );
};
```

