TITLE: Using useMedia Hook in React Component
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the useMedia hook to track a CSS media query for responsive design. The example checks if the screen width is at least 480px.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useMedia.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useMedia} from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  const isWide = useMedia('(min-width: 480px)');

  return (
    <div>
      Screen is wide: {isWide ? 'Yes' : 'No'}
    </div>
  );
};
```

