TITLE: Implementing useGetSet Hook for Asynchronous State Updates in React
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use the useGetSet hook to correctly increment a counter after a 1-second delay on each button click. It prevents issues that can occur with nested functions in asynchronous operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useGetSet.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useGetSet} from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  const [get, set] = useGetSet(0);
  const onClick = () => {
    setTimeout(() => {
      set(get() + 1)
    }, 1_000);
  };

  return (
    <button onClick={onClick}>Clicked: {get()}</button>
  );
};
```

