TITLE: Basic useKeyPress Hook Implementation in React JSX
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the useKeyPress hook to detect when users press number keys from 0 to 9. The example renders the pressed numbers with plus signs between them when multiple keys are pressed simultaneously.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useKeyPress.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useKeyPress} from 'react-use';

const keys = ['1', '2', '3', '4', '5', '6', '7', '8', '9', '0'];

const Demo = () => {
  const states = [];
  for (const key of keys) states.push(useKeyPress(key)[0]);

  return (
    <div style={{textAlign: 'center'}}>
      Try pressing numbers
      <br />
      {states.reduce((s, pressed, index) => s + (pressed ? (s ? ' + ' : '') + keys[index] : ''), '')}
    </div>
  );
};
```

