TITLE: Implementing useHash Hook in React
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the useHash hook to track and modify browser location hash. The example shows setting an initial hash value on mount and creating an input field to dynamically update the hash. The hook returns the current hash value and a setter function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useHash.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useHash} from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  const [hash, setHash] = useHash();

  useMount(() => {
    setHash('#/path/to/page?userId=123');
  });

  return (
    <div>
      <div>window.location.href:</div>
      <div>
        <pre>{window.location.href}</pre>
      </div>
      <div>Edit hash: </div>
      <div>
        <input style={{ width: '100%' }} value={hash} onChange={e => setHash(e.target.value)} />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

