TITLE: Using useEffectOnce Hook in React Component
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to use useEffectOnce hook to run an effect once on component mount and cleanup on unmount. The hook takes an effect callback that executes on mount and can return a cleanup function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useEffectOnce.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useEffectOnce} from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  useEffectOnce(() => {
    console.log('Running effect once on mount')

    return () => {
      console.log('Running clean-up of effect on unmount')
    }
  });

  return null;
};
```

