TITLE: Implementing State Validation with useStateValidator in React
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the useStateValidator hook to validate user input for even numbers. It includes a custom validator function and renders an input field with validation feedback.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useStateValidator.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import * as React from 'react';
import { useCallback } from 'react';
import { useStateValidator } from 'react-use';

const DemoStateValidator = s => [s === '' ? null : (s * 1) % 2 === 0];
const Demo = () => {
