TITLE: Implementing Window Resize Handler with useRafState Hook in React
DESCRIPTION: Example demonstrating how to use useRafState hook to track window dimensions. The state updates are synchronized with requestAnimationFrame for better performance. Uses useMount for lifecycle management and includes cleanup to prevent memory leaks.
SOURCE: https://github.com/streamich/react-use/blob/master/docs/useRafState.md#2025-04-21_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import {useRafState, useMount} from 'react-use';

const Demo = () => {
  const [state, setState] = useRafState({
    width: 0,
    height: 0,
  });

  useMount(() => {
    const onResize = () => {
      setState({
        width: window.clientWidth,
        height: window.height,
      });
    };

    window.addEventListener('resize', onResize);

    return () => {
      window.removeEventListener('resize', onResize);
    };
  });

  return <pre>{JSON.stringify(state, null, 2)}</pre>;
};
```

